'Maintenance Technician to support operations by maintaining ' 'our Service Centers and equipment. We are looking for an ' 'individual who can work independently while at the same time ' 'possessing the ability to use common sense to accomplish the ' 'tasks required, efficiently and effectively. Someone who is ' 'self-motivated and willing to step in and help wherever ' 'necessary.

Duties and ' 'Responsibilities:

    \t
  • Operate large, ' 'powered machinery and equipment (e.g., saws, drills, ' 'grinders, blowtorches, pressure cleaners, jackhammers, and ' 'power tools
    • \t
  • Perform all aspects of property ' 'maintenance, including preventative, corrective, deferred and ' 'emergency maintenance
    • \t
  • Maintain all maintenance ' 'shops and storage rooms in an orderly fashion and in ' 'compliance with safety regulations
    • \t
  • Maintain ' 'accurate inventory control of tools, equipment, and ' 'supplies
    • \t
  • Perform maintenance inspections and ' 'repairs on the service center building and on the service ' 'center equipment
    • \t
  • Assist the maintenance team on ' 'special maintenance projects; preventive maintenance of ' 'building components and/or mechanicals
    • \t
  • Serve as ' 'on-call maintenance for emergencies when needed
    • \t' '
  • Perform all other duties as assigned

' '

Qualification:

    \t' '
  • Maintenance knowledge is imperative along with the ' 'capability to assess health and safety requirements
    • \t' '
  • Have multi-unit building maintenance experience
    • \t' '
  • Electrical/plumbing knowledge preferred
    • \t
  • Must ' 'demonstrate consistency in quality of work
    • \t
  • Ability ' 'and willingness to take direction and follow through as ' 'directed
    • \t
  • Must be able to multi-task
    • \t' '
  • Ability to work independently, managing multiple tasks ' 'while maintaining a positive attitude

' '

Physical Requirements:

    \t' '
  • Able to work in all types of weather
    • \t' '
  • Flexibility, frequent bending, stooping, squatting, ' 'crawling, and climbing activities
    • \t
  • Lifting and ' 'carrying of bulky or heavy items
    • \t
  • Able to work on ' 'your feet for extended periods

' '

Additional Requirements:

    \t' "
  • 2-3 years' experience in multi-unit commercial facility " 'maintenance
    • \t
  • Preferred experience with hydraulics ' 'electrical and pneumatic
    • \t
  • Ability to pass a ' 'background check
    • \t
  • Valid, Florida driver ' 'license
    • \t
  • Daily travel between job sites and out of ' 'state travel as needed (company van provided)

' '

Company benefits include:

  • PTO

    • \t
  • 401k with company ' 'match
    • \t
  • Employee discounts on personal vehicle
    • \t' '
  • Cell phone allowance

Salary to commensurate ' 'with experience
